                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 7661/1.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Beaupré</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Buenos Aires</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1907-07-19">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 19, 1907</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>(Mr. Beaupré states that the Government’s analysis of deviled ham shows a small
                    quantity of boric acid, and that time has been granted for reshipment until an
                    investigation has been made. Says he will send samples.)</p>
            </div>
        </body>
